Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, add the @penne pasta{180%g} to your pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

While the pasta cooks, thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}.

Once the beef is browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Stir in the @Provencal herbs{1} and mushrooms.

Cook for another ~{2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Worcester sauce{15%ml} and simmer until evaporated.

Stir in the @finely chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}, @sugar{1} and @red wine jus paste{15%g}.

Bring to the boil then reduce the heat and simmer until thick, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Stir the @baby spinach{100%g} through the sauce a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} then add to the sauce. Stir to combine.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if your sauce needs loosening.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then serve the penne ragu in bowls.

Sprinkle with the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Enjoy!